name: TheAtlantic
text: Some dispatches from this strange election purgatory, in the latest Atlantic Daily by @mimbsy: https://t.co/MdJEqj9HzP

name: TheAtlantic
text: "How long could this take? It might be a couple more hours. Or another day. A week of Tuesdays has already passed," @IsaacDovere reports from Wilmington: https://t.co/Id9yLclCdx

name: TheAtlantic
text: RT @AdrienneLaF: A quote for the ages: “What I am enjoying is that the most famously anti-science, anti-factual president of my lifetime is now being slowly taught mathematics, and the inescapable consequences of mathematics." @IsaacDovere's latest, just published https://t.co/hcd9yfIIKb

name: TheAtlantic
text:
RT @realcpaz: Lots of great detail in @IsaacDovere’s dispatch from Biden camp—read it:

“His aides are determined to give him at least one big, happy speech. They want to do it for a man who has spent 50 years dreaming of the presidency...”

https://t.co/5o5zng5uWj

name: TheAtlantic
text: International observers have been a part of American democracy for nearly two decades. The leader of the OSCE's observer mission told @YasmeenSerhan that this election is "definitely one for the memoirs." https://t.co/DlyZCSXgk7
